Police: Man nearly caused crashes walking the center line
Comment
By Diane Turbyfill dturbyfill@gastongazette.com
Gaston Gazette
By Diane Turbyfill dturbyfill@gastongazette.com
Posted May. 3, 2016 at 7:47 AM
Updated at 7:47 AM
By Diane Turbyfill dturbyfill@gastongazette.com
Posted May. 3, 2016 at 7:47 AM
A man almost caused multiple accidents when he walked the center line on a county highway Monday night, police say.A Gaston County police officer spotted the 20-year-old man around 8:45 p.m. on Dallas Stanley Highway near the intersection of Spencer Mountain Road, according to arrest reports.The officer said Billy Lamar Cherry III appeared intoxicated while walking the yellow line delaying traffic and nearly causing car crashes.Cherry, 20, of Stanley, was charged with being intoxicated and disruptive and jailed on a $500 bond.Cherry has prior convictions of felony larceny, breaking and entering and possession of drug paraphernalia for which he was sentenced to probation.He was charged with probation violations twice in 2014, according to the Gaston County Sheriff's Office website.
By Diane Turbyfill dturbyfill@gastongazette.com
Gaston Gazette
By Diane Turbyfill dturbyfill@gastongazette.com
